hrough the title character's interaction with the patriarchy. Through these connections, it responds to a growing current in German Studies concerned with diversity and inclusion and integrating the discipline into the broader humanities. An introduction and an afterword, both of them extensive and scholarly, contextualize the novel in its time and as it relates to ours.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aGerman Literature. 4aModern History. 4aModern Literature. 4aWomen's & Gender Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  a#MeToo.  aBlack Lives Matter.  aCaribbean island.  aChicago.  aGerman Studies.  aHarlem Renaissance.  aJim Crow.  aNew York City.  aWomen's Studies.  adiversity and inclusion.  ahybrid identities.  amigration.  amixed-race woman.  apassing as white.  apatriarchy.  aracial attitudes.  astructural racism.1 aHöyng, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöyng, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLayne, Priscilla D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLayne, Priscilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMellor, Chauncey J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMellor, Chauncey J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311143099740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800106796?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800106796423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800106796/original  a978-3-11-143099-7  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles